I"\
<p><strong>Example:</strong> Let $U_1$ and $U_2$ be independent, each having the Uniform[0,1]
distribution. We write this as $U_1, U_2$ are i.i.d. Uniform[0,1].</p>

<p>Then define X and Y by</p>

\[X=\sqrt{2 \log \left(1 / U_{1}\right)} \cos \left(2 \pi U_{2}\right), \quad
Y=\sqrt{2 \log \left(1 / U_{1}\right)} \sin \left(2 \pi U_{2}\right)\]

